cluster_relations.rel_desc: The rapid advancement of Artificial Intelligence is described as bringing about numerous ethical dilemmas in AI development.

qualifiers.OperationalConstraint: in the development and deployment of AI technologies
qualifiers.OtherQualifier: ImpactScope: affecting various industries and aspects of daily life

cluster_relations.rel_desc: Opacity of AI systems contributes to a lack of transparency.
remarks: Relation added to capture implied semantic link between opacity and non-transparency.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Subject is a causal or enabling factor that contributes to the occurrence or presence of the object, without implying it is the sole cause.
args.justification: Both relations describe a causal contribution: the rapid advancement of AI contributing to ethical dilemmas, and opacity of AI systems contributing to lack of transparency. Normalizing "gives_rise_to" and "contributes_to" under one predicate "contributes_to" provides a consistent causal contribution edge without overcommitting to strict determinism.

Both relations link a cause-like factor (AI advancement, system opacity) to a resulting situation (ethical dilemmas, lack of transparency). They belong to the same family of causal influence relations where one factor influences the emergence of another.
The rel_hint_type is "causal" and the descriptions clearly frame subject entities as contributing causes of the object entities, so both belong in the broad CAUSALITY group.
